events.description:

events.title: December 2025 CINLUG Meeting — Btrfs
events.description:
CINLUG | Central Indiana Linux Users Group
Btrfs has been the default file system for openSUSE since openSuSE 13.2 in 2014. Fedora Linux followed suit in late 2020 with Fedora Linux 33. Just this year, Alma Linux started supporting Btrfs in version 10.1 of their distribution.

Come to Central INdiana Linux User Group's (CINLUG's) December meeting to learn more about this next generation file system where Neal Gompa[1] will provide an overview of it, a bit of its history, and how to get started u
